The paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for video reconstruction of live cells captured using Fourier ptychographic microscopy (FPM). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves statistical learning from spatial ensembles, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper proposes a novel CNN framework, which could also place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category.
